                     <interp inst="t18220911-303-person2709" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I know the prisoner by seeing her in the Haymarket Theatre. On Monday the 16th, I saw her; she invited me to go to Edmonton Fair with her the following day, and said a gentleman gave her two sovereigns.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. She knew the watch was not my own, and persuaded me to go and sell it in Rosemary-lane; but I pawned it, and bought her a gown and a pair of earrings. The gentleman gave it me instead of money.</p>
